    <string name="dialog_text_off_after_disc_timeout"><b>Experimental.</b> With this preference, Wi-Fi will be turned off after certain time of disconnection. \
This will shorten the time needed to turn off Wi-Fi when leaving Wi-Fi reach.\n\n\
However this might not be as good idea as it seems, as Wi-Fi will not be turned on automatically if you return to Wi-Fi reach without having left the location where the Wi-Fi is registered.</string>
    <string name="preference_title_mobile_data_managed">Disable mobile data</string>
    <string name="preference_summary_mobile_data_managed">While connected to a known Wi-Fi</string>
    <string name="dialog_text_mobile_data_managed"><b>Important Warning.</b> With this option, if mobile data setting is initially enabled, it will be deactivated while connected to a known Wi-Fi network and it will be activated back after it is disconnected from Wi-Fi.\n\n\
Turning on mobile data may cause additional charges to your account. Use this option at your own risk.</string>
    <string name="preference_title_unk_location_activates_wifi">Activate Wi-Fi if no coverage</string>   
    <string name="preference_summary_unk_location_activates_wifi">Activate in places with no mobile coverage</string>
    <string name="dialog_text_unk_location_activates_wifi">Wi-Fi Matic needs mobile coverage to know where your device is. With this option Wi-Fi will be activated in all places where the device loses mobile network coverage.\n\n\
This might be the best option if you don\'t have any coverage where your Wi-Fi network is, although it might increase battery usage.</string>
    
    <!-- Welcome dialog -->
    <string name="dialog_text_welcome_1"><b>Welcome to Wi-Fi Matic!</b>\n\n\
Wi-Fi Matic activates and deactivates Wi-Fi of your device automatically, depending on your location, helping to save battery and consumption of data \
through your operator network.\n\n\
This wizard will help you to setup Wi-Fi Matic with three simple steps.</string>
    <string name="dialog_text_welcome_2"><b>Step 1:</b>\n\nSelect <b>Enable Wi-Fi Matic</b> to activate and deactivate Wi-Fi of your device automatically.</string>
    <string name="dialog_text_welcome_3a"><b>Step 2:</b>\n\nYou are currently not connected to any Wi-Fi network. Select <b>Wi-Fi settings</b> to connect to a network you have access and let Wi-Fi Matic remember its location. Select back button when you are done.\n\n\
You can do it later from <b>Settings -&gt; Wireless and network</b> Android menu.</string>
    <string name="dialog_text_welcome_3b">&lt;b&gt;Step 2:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You are currently connected to Wi-Fi network: &lt;b&gt;%s&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Wi-Fi Matic will remember its location.</string>    
    <string name="dialog_text_welcome_4"><b>Step 3:</b>\n\nAnd that\'s all! Select <b>Finish</b> to exit this wizard and go back to Wi-Fi Matic.\n\n\
For more information you can go to <b>Info</b> from the application menu.</string>
    <string name="dialog_button_welcome_next">Next &gt;&gt;</string>
